Six members of one family, including a minor, were killed in their home by an armed group in central Mexico, the local prosecutor’s office has said. Gunmen arrived at the house in Celaya in Guanajuato state on Thursday night and started setting off “explosions targeting the family,” it added. Investigators found three women and two men dead at the scene, as well as a minor whose age and gender was not given, the prosecutor’s office said Friday. READ ALSO: How PDP govs, chieftains endorsed Obaseki, Shaibu ticket Two other women were wounded and taken to hospital, according to the state security ministry. Celaya’s mayor condemned the killings and said he would help with the investigation. Guanajuato is one of Mexico’s main industrial centers and has attracted the attention of violent cartels involved in drug trafficking, extortion, kidnapping and stealing petrol. (AFP)